{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619891"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:37:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:37:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16584"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16584","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16584"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.78,0.06,0.09,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9275"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66042"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9275","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9275"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16584"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51499"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"873"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3169"},{"type":"tags","id":"3189"},{"type":"tags","id":"3320"},{"type":"tags","id":"3343"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"7102"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21970"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21983"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22079"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45768"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66042"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 64-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with progressive confusion and personality changes over the past six weeks. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears unwell with impaired cognitive function. Her vital signs are within normal limits. Neurological examination reveals no focal deficits. Magnetic resonance imaging of the brain shows an irregularly enhancing mass with central necrosis and surrounding vasogenic oedema in the right frontal lobe.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acoustic neuroma","Glioblastoma multiforme","Medulloblastoma","Meningioma","Pituitary adenoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation and imaging findings are highly suggestive of glioblastoma multiforme (GBM). The characteristic imaging features of \u003Cstrong\u003Eglioblastoma multiforme\u003C/strong\u003E include irregular enhancement, central necrosis, and surrounding vasogenic oedema. The rapid onset of symptoms and poor prognosis (median survival 12-15 months with treatment) are also typical of GBM.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPituitary adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E typically present with endocrine symptoms and visual field defects due to their location in the sellar region. They demonstrate homogeneous enhancement and rarely show necrosis or significant oedema.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeningiomas\u003C/strong\u003E are typically extra-axial tumours with a dural tail sign, homogeneous enhancement, and clear margins. They usually grow slowly and rarely cause such rapid cognitive decline.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcoustic neuromas\u003C/strong\u003E arise from the vestibular nerve in the internal auditory canal and typically present with unilateral hearing loss and tinnitus. They are well-circumscribed and show homogeneous enhancement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedulloblastomas\u003C/strong\u003E typically occur in children and arise in the posterior fossa. They usually present with symptoms of increased intracranial pressure and cerebellar dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Glioblastoma multiforme typically presents with cognitive impairment and has characteristic imaging findings of irregular enhancement with central necrosis and surrounding vasogenic oedema.","Glioblastoma multiforme has a poor prognosis with median survival of 12-15 months with treatment.","The presence of necrosis and irregular enhancement pattern helps distinguish glioblastoma from other intracranial tumours."],"references":["Li J, Feng L, Lu Y. Glioblastoma multiforme: Diagnosis, treatment, and invasion. J Biomed Res. 2022 Oct 28;37(1):47-58. doi: 10.7555/JBR.36.20220156. PMID: 36403983; PMCID: PMC9898042.","Wu W, Klockow JL, Zhang M, Lafortune F, Chang E, Jin L, Wu Y, Daldrup-Link HE. Glioblastoma multiforme (GBM): An overview of current therapies and mechanisms of resistance. Pharmacol Res. 2021 Sep;171:105780. doi: 10.1016/j.phrs.2021.105780. Epub 2021 Jul 21. PMID: 34302977; PMCID: PMC8384724.","Davis ME. Glioblastoma: Overview of Disease and Treatment. Clin J Oncol Nurs. 2016 Oct 1;20(5 Suppl):S2-8. doi: 10.1188/16.CJON.S1.2-8. PMID: 27668386; PMCID: PMC5123811."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51499"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16584"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51499"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-29T08:58:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-29T08:58:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9275"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66042"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":